Tiebreak finals


[Nov 29]
Palestra Itália  1-2  Atlético 
[Carazzo 57'; Geraldino 20', Chaffir 72']

SSPI: Catalano; Nereu, Gil; Maeco, Barros, Calixto;
Piorra, Niginho, Carazzo, Bengala, Alcides. Coach: Matturi Fabbi
CAM: Armando; Maurílio, Nariz; Cordeiro, Brant, Mário Gomes;
Geraldino, Jairo, Orlando Vaz, Chaffir, Cunha. Coach: Marinetti

[Dec 6]
Atlético         n/p   Palestra Itália (*)

(*) This match did not start due to the absence of a neutral referee
from Rio de Janeiro - an Atlético responsibility, as agreed between
the teams. Atlético appointed three other names, but Palestra did
not agree and felt threatened at the opponent's stadium.

The Federation tried to reschedule this match but Palestra broke
off the relationship with Atlético and abandoned the Federation,
following Villa Nova, América and Sete de Setembro. In 1932 the
dissident clubs would assemble their own league and championships.

Therefore, the Federation proclaimed:

** Atlético are the Minas Gerais champions of 1931 **
*** Topscorer: Orlando (Atlético) 18 goals ***

